Outlet.description: The Outlet schema contains definition for an electrical outlet.
Outlet.longDescription: This resource shall be used to represent an electrical outlet for a Redfish implementation.

enumLongDescriptions.PowerCycle: This value shall indicate the resource will transition to a power off state, then transition to a power on state.  Upon successful completion, the PowerState property, if supported, shall contain the value `On`.

enumLongDescriptions.BS_1363_Type_G: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the British BS 1363 Type G receptacle (250V; 13A).
enumLongDescriptions.BusConnection: This value shall represent a direct connection to an electrical bus.
enumLongDescriptions.CEE_7_Type_E: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the French specified CEE 7/7 Type E receptacle (250V; 16A).
enumLongDescriptions.CEE_7_Type_F: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the Schuko specified CEE 7/7 Type F receptacle (250V; 16A).
enumLongDescriptions.IEC_60320_C13: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the IEC 60320 Sheet F C13 specified receptacle (250V; 10A per IEC, 15A per UL).
enumLongDescriptions.IEC_60320_C19: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the IEC 60320 Sheet J C19 specified receptacle (250V; 16A per IEC, 20A per UL).
enumLongDescriptions.NEMA_5_15R: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the NEMA specified 5-15 receptacle (120V; 15A).  The current is commonly de-rated to 12A if it is protected by a 15A breaker.
enumLongDescriptions.NEMA_5_20R: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the NEMA specified 5-20 receptacle that exhibits a T-slot (120V; 20A).  The current is commonly de-rated to 16A if it is protected by a 20A breaker.
enumLongDescriptions.NEMA_L5_20R: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the NEMA specified locking L5-20 receptacle (120V; 20A).  The current is commonly de-rated to 16A if it is protected by a 20A breaker.
enumLongDescriptions.NEMA_L5_30R: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the NEMA specified locking L5-30 receptacle (120V; 30A).  The current is commonly de-rated to 24A if it is protected by a 30A breaker.
enumLongDescriptions.NEMA_L6_20R: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the NEMA specified locking L6-20 receptacle (250V; 20A).  The current is commonly de-rated to 16A if it is protected by a 20A breaker.
enumLongDescriptions.NEMA_L6_30R: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the NEMA specified locking L6-30 receptacle (250V; 30A).  The current is commonly de-rated to 24A if it is protected by a 30A breaker.
enumLongDescriptions.SEV_1011_TYPE_12: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the SEV 1011 specified Type 12 receptacle (250V; 10A).
enumLongDescriptions.SEV_1011_TYPE_23: This value shall represent a receptacle that matches the SEV 1011 specified Type 23 receptacle (250V; 16A).
